title: SpaceX launches eighth dedicated smallsat rideshare mission
summary: SpaceX's Transporter-8 mission launched 72 payloads, including satellites from established companies like Spire, Iceye, and Satellogic, as well as first-time satellite deployments from startups such as Varda Space Industries, Satellite Vu, and Muon Space. The mission also carried satellites for the U.S. Space Force and DARPA.
